## Introduction > This dataset contains information about 10,000 movies collected from The Movie Database (TMDb), including user ratings and revenue. > By using the dataset, some interesting questions will be answersed, such as which genres are most popular from year to year? What kinds of properties are associated with movies that have high revenues?

## Data Cleaning ### Drop the null data of important information

#   cleaned, perform those cleaning steps in the second part of this section.
df.dropna(subset=['imdb_id', 'cast', 'genres', "budget_adj", "revenue_adj", "budget", "revenue"], inplace=True)

### Drop some unreasonable data

# These values of the movie cannot be zero
df = df[df.budget != 0]
df = df[df.revenue != 0]
df = df[df.budget_adj != 0]
df = df[df.revenue_adj != 0]

df.describe()

## Exploratory Data Analysis ### Research Question 1ï¼šwhich genres are most popular through these years? The first interesting question will be finding the most popular genres through all these years.
From the plot shown above, the most popular genres of these moives are drama, comedy and thriller.

### Research Question 3: what kinds of properties are associated with movies that have high revenues? To investigate moives have high revenues, the revenue_adj of the associated movie is used, it can account for inflation over time.
df['revenue_adj'].describe()
Then the relationships between the "popularity", "vote_average", "budget_adj" and "revenue_adj" will be investigated.
df2 = df[['popularity', 'vote_average', 'budget_adj', 'revenue_adj']]
The sns.pairplot will be used to show pairwise relationships in the dataset
plot2 = sns.pairplot(df2, kind="reg", diag_kind="kde", size=3)
From the plot shown above, the "popularity", "vote_average", and "budget_adj" have positive correlation with the "revenue_adj".
### Research Question 4: How did the produced moives changed over time? Finally, the trend of produced moives changed over time will be invesitaged.

From the plots shown above, the trend of produced moives numbers and geners types can be clearly viewed. Basically, the number of movies are growing over time, and the numbers of drama and mustery movies are increased significantly.

## Conclusions Firstly, the cleaning of the dataset has been made. The null values and duplicated values have been removed from the dataset. Then several plots have been made to investigate several problems: 1. Ten most popular movies through these years have been found. 2. The most popular movie genres of each year have been found. 3. The properties associated with high revenues movies have been investigated. 4. The number of movies and the numbers of genres changed through time have been studied. ### Limitations 1. TMBD Movies dataset has been used for our analysis, but this data contains a lot of missing values, during the analysis, I have to abandon these missing data, that can not give us a full picture of the movies or even can show unintentional bias results. A method to treat the null values need to be considered. 2. The normalization or currency conversion has not been considered during the analysis. The information of budget or revenue did not contain their currency type or exchange rate. That will caused problems if we wrongly treat them as the same kind of currency or even skew our analysis. 3. The dataset only provides parts of the movie information. If we can find more detailed data about these movies, that will greatly improve our analysis. For example, if the dataset can provide the awards received by actors or directors, it will help us to get better understanding of properties are associated with movies that have high revenues or high popularity.
